main event: A rectangular object 50-60 feet long and 8-12 feet high was observed hovering above the ground for approximately 22 minutes in Eutaw, Alabama on October 19, 1962.
interesting points: The object appeared to be spinning steadily and had a mass of blinking lights, but made no sound.
The object climbed rapidly and disappeared at dawn.
The nature, origin, and purpose of the object could not be determined based on the available information.
There was no physical evidence left behind, such as a trace on the ground.
The Air Force concluded the object was possibly a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical in nature, but there was insufficient data for a definitive evaluation.
